RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Drum major
<hw>Drum" ma"jor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr><def>.</def> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
chief or first drummer of a regiment; an instructor of
drummers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The marching leader of a military band.</def>
<mark>[U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A noisy gathering. <mark>[R.]</mark> See under
<er>Drum</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 4.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Drummer</ent>⟦br⟧
